  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial package contains a broken provenance link on the primary validation result: the most narratively detailed ValidationResult omits its prov:wasGeneratedBy Activity reference, creating an epistemic gap that a reviewer might overlook because the prose narrative describes the experimental campaign in sufficient detail to appear self-sufficient.",
